    <div class="container-dolphin py-12 md:py-16 max-w-4xl">

      <div class="bg-navy/5 border-l-4 border-gold rounded-r-lg p-4 mb-6">
        <p class="text-sm text-text-light leading-relaxed italic">Dolphin Centrifuge maintains a rental fleet of Alfa Laval disc stack centrifuges for process evaluation, emergency service, and short-term capacity augmentation. Rental disc centrifuges cover diesel fuel purification, coolant recovery, waste oil reclamation, lube oil clarification, and industrial liquid/solid separation. Based in Warren, Michigan — call (248) 522-2573 for rental availability and pricing.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Legacy Content (verbatim) -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-10">
        <p class="text-text-light mb-4">
          Dolphin Centrifuge maintains a fleet of Rental Disc-stack Centrifuges that are suited for:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-text-light space-y-1 mb-4">
          <li>&#8226; Centrifuge Evaluation for your specific process</li>
          <li>&#8226; Emergency Service in case your centrifuge breaks down or is in service</li>
          <li>&#8226; Short-term process capacity augmentation</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-text-light mb-6">
          In some cases, Dolphin Centrifuge can accommodate long-term rental requirements by building a skid for specific customer applications.
        </p>
        <p class="text-text-light font-semibold">
          A rental contract requires a minimum rental period commitment, deposit, execution of a formal rental contract, and other standard conditions.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- MAPX 207 Disc Stack Centrifuge Rental -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold font-heading text-navy mb-4">MAPX 207 Disc Stack Centrifuge Rental</h2>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-4">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy mb-3">Applications</h3>
        <ul class="text-text-light space-y-1 mb-6">
          <li>&#8226; Diesel Fuel</li>
          <li>&#8226; Engine Oil</li>
          <li>&#8226; Hydraulic Oil</li>
          <li>&#8226; Light Crude Oil</li>
          <li>&#8226; Waste Oil &ndash; Used Oil</li>
