        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-navy mb-2">What disc stack centrifuge models are available for rental?</h3>
            <p class="text-text-light text-sm">Dolphin Centrifuge offers rental of DMPX-series self-cleaning disc stack centrifuges ranging from DMPX-010 (7 GPM) to DMPX-070 (59–72 GPM on diesel). Units are available as standalone centrifuge skids or as complete systems with controls, pumps, and heating. Contact us for current availability.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-navy mb-2">What are the common reasons to rent a disc stack centrifuge?</h3>
            <p class="text-text-light text-sm">Common rental use cases include: pilot testing before a capital purchase decision, emergency backup during a machine rebuild, temporary capacity for seasonal production spikes, project work at a site without permanent equipment, and proving a new application before committing to permanent installation.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-navy mb-2">Can I rent a centrifuge to test my application before buying?</h3>
            <p class="text-text-light text-sm">Yes. Dolphin Centrifuge rental programs are specifically designed for application validation. You can rent a DMPX-series centrifuge, run it on your process fluid at your facility, and evaluate separation quality and throughput before making a purchase decision. Our sample testing service can also pre-qualify your fluid in our lab.</p>
          </div>
